Subject: [PATCH 37/39] Make timesyncd a "simple" service

the daemon ends up waiting 100 msec on networking conditions before notifying
that it is done, even though that's really not relevant
---
 units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in b/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in
index 8d328bb80..3122aec04 100644
--- a/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in
+++ b/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in
@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@ Conflicts=shutdown.target
 Wants=time-sync.target
 
 [Service]
-Type=notify
+Type=simple
 Restart=always
 RestartSec=0
 ExecStart=@rootlibexecdir@/systemd-timesyncd
